data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**The sync-over-async opt-in for EF Core's Cosmos DB provider is completely removed.** In .NET 11, calling any synchronous I/O API on the Cosmos provider **always throws** â€” there is no configuration to restore the old behavior.

### Affected methods in your code:

| Broken call | Fix |
|---|---|
| `.ToList()` | `await .ToListAsync()` |
| `.First(...)` | `await .FirstAsync(...)` |
| `.Count()` | `await .CountAsync()` |
| `.SaveChanges()` | `await .SaveChangesAsync()` |

### Required fix:

Convert the repository to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
        => await _context.Products.ToListAsync();

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
        => await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
        => await _context.Products.CountAsync();

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This is a **source-breaking** change â€” all callers up the chain must also become async (`async Task`/`async Task<T>`). There is no workaround; the Cosmos SDK is async-only and EF Core 11 no longer wraps it.

**Tracking issue:** https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059
